{"TopicId":206268,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"[complete!] 111 Days","CreatedByName":"OrbitalManeuvers","CreatedById":190887,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T07:11:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalManeuvers","CreatedById":190887,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T07:11:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo this is my first post to this forum, and not what I had planned. But I think I have discovered an interesting situation, and if I\u0027m seeing it correctly, I think it might make a fun mission report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you help me figure out if this is what I think it is?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTonight was the first time I\u0027ve ever tracked an asteroid. The second one I selected is shown below (I resized in the post, but I think you can click for full size?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I may point out the obvious:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nthe asteroid I\u0027m tracking is the yellow orbit\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEarth (KSRSS at 2.5x) is the blue orbit\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nthe asteroid has an encounter with Earth shortly after its periapsis. wut wut.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022cp00Obi.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/cp00Obi.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere I\u0027ll zoom into the encounter. Notice there\u0027s no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E marker on this orbit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u0022Lri7CZ2.png\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Lri7CZ2.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nZooming in farther...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KHCqHcG.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/KHCqHcG.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, unless I\u0027m mistaken, there are 111 days until the potential end of our species? Obviously I saved this game under the name Deep Impact as soon as I saw this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have questions! Is this common? Does this seem interesting? Do you think it\u0027d be fun to ... errrrrm ... IDEK?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have zero exposure to the asteroid mechanics in game, and have no idea what happens when an asteroid intersects - I assume the asteroid just disappears? But does something actually enter the atmosphere? Clearly I would need to be flying in the area at the time. Or on a boat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway - please share any thoughts about this potential(?) mission! And honestly, if this happens every 3rd time you start a new game I\u0027m not gonna be that into it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Watermel00n","CreatedById":217752,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T09:58:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlies right through.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Randazzo","CreatedById":136468,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T11:51:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you intercept it and ride it down. Then it bounces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T12:13:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you have to \u0022save the planet\u0022, you only save the asteroid \u2014 so don\u0027t worry, KSP will delete the space rock before it hits the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalManeuvers","CreatedById":190887,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T15:35:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224072985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641376700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Watermel00n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Watermel00n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlies right through.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073028\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641384805\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you have to \u0022save the planet\u0022, you only save the asteroid\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha ... I kinda figured my hopes were too high. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EDANGIT. At least I had something that \u003Cem\u003Elooked\u003C/em\u003E dramatic in the tracking station!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T16:20:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut i would still enjoy seeing a mission to save the planet!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T16:26:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641399624\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210882\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Maria Sirona\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Maria Sirona said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut i would still enjoy seeing a mission to save the planet!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen edit \u003Cem\u003Epotatoroid.cfg\u003C/em\u003E somewhere in your game files so it doesn\u0027t explode due to overheating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr redirect a bigger asteroid, perhaps a class H or I.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr both. (Woooow, I\u0027d like to see that!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalManeuvers","CreatedById":190887,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T17:20:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073119\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641399624\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210882\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Maria Sirona\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, Maria Sirona said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut i would still enjoy seeing a mission to save the planet!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly, ME TOO. I fear I may be a bit smooth-brained for this, but maybe with some help. I\u0027ve already spent a minute in the tracking station and with a craft in orbit, and neither MechJeb nor I have any clue how to get to this thing.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224073126\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206268\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221641399973\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217956\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nazalassa\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, Nazalassa said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr redirect a bigger asteroid, perhaps a class H or I.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis one happens to be a Class H. It\u0027s currently zipping along at 14km/s, and is about equidistant from its \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E now as to when it will impact Earth, so should be about that same speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelp, time to hunt for some tutorial videos!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nazalassa","CreatedById":217956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T17:22:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you didn\u0027t change \u003Cem\u003Epotatoroid.cfg\u003C/em\u003E, the asteroid will just burn, and explose... No need for a mission, let the nature do it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-05T22:32:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGet your dinos to their bomb shelters.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalManeuvers","CreatedById":190887,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T02:00:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, not wanting to disappoint anyone, I took a stab at this. The results were exactly as expected for not knowing anything about wrangling asteroids!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022R88Z8DH.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/R88Z8DH.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI honestly had no idea what this would involve but here I am with 3400m/s, and my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E is probably around 4.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Ddwhqty.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Ddwhqty.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAND THEN I GRABBED IT\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I think you know that with 7m/s I wasn\u0027t moving that thing anywhere.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022SrWmM1c.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/SrWmM1c.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I proudly present the final moments of my first asteroid:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQ2C4IUo8hc?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for tuning in \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-06T08:35:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat editing and choice of music\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}